The paper deals with concurrent data structures and their correctness conditions, which are typically studied in the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) and Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the scalability issues of linearizability, which is a property of concurrent data structures that is relevant to the Programming Languages (cs.PL) and Operating Systems (cs.OS) sub-categories. Finally, the paper introduces a hierarchy of strengthened variants of sequential consistency, which is a topic that falls under the Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO) sub-category.
